Two ssh methods to save your energy
I highly recommend using the methods in both link to save your time!

ssh-keygen will save the process of typing login passwords
Check this website https://www.thegeekstuff.com/2008/11/3-steps-to-perform-ssh-login-without-password-using-ssh-keygen-ssh-copy-id/

.ssh/config will save the process of typing passwords when syncing files!
# Note this method will also save the two-factor authentication!
Check this website https://hcc.unl.edu/docs/connecting/reusing_ssh_connections_in_linux_or_mac/#:~:text=To%20enable%20connection%2[â€¦]0if%20possible%E2%80%9D%20checkbox 
